Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Pop onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil, season with @salt and @pepper then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and slightly charred, ~{15-18%mins}. Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%mins}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly. Add the onion and cook until softened, ~{3-4%mins}. Stir in the @chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%can}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and @chicken stock powder{1%tsp}, then lower the heat and simmer gently until thickened, ~{8-10%mins}.

> Add a splash of water to loosen if needed.

While the sauce simmers, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to your pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}. Once the pepper has roasted, stir it into the sauce.

While the pasta cooks, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @ciabatta{1} and lay onto the (now empty) pepper baking tray, cut-side up. Spread over the garlic and drizzle with the @olive oil{for garlic bread}. Sprinkle over half the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated). Bake the garlic bread on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{5-6%mins}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @chives{1} (use #scissors{} if easier). Once cooked, drain the pasta in a #colander{} and stir into the sauce. Stir through the remaining hard Italian style cheese and half the chives.

> Add another splash of water to loosen if needed.

Spoon the pasta into your #bowls{}. Finish with a sprinkle of the remaining chives and a pinch of @chilli flakes{1%pinch} over the top for those who'd like some heat (be careful, they're hot). Slice the ciabatta diagonally into triangles and serve alongside. Enjoy!